<h2>Privacy</h2>
<p>PFD is committed to protecting the privacy of visitors to its website. Except in the circumstances set out in this Privacy Statement, PFD will not attempt to identify you. Your name and other identifying personal details are not collected (unless you specifically provide them to us).</p>
<p>PFD gathers information on this website in 3 ways;</p>
<p><strong>1. Information is gathered indirectly through the site’s technology</strong></p>
<p>When you look at our website, our standard practice is not to monitor any of your browsing activities. From time to time, PFD may make a statistical record of that visit and logs the information for the purpose of evaluating our website. The types of information we collect may be:</p>
<ul>
<li>your server address only (for example, 203.147.56.66)</li>
<li>your top level domain name (for example, .com, .gov, .au, .uk)</li>
<li>the date and time of your visit to the site</li>
<li>the pages you accessed and documents downloaded</li>
<li>the type of browser you are using</li>
<li>the previous site you visited</li>
</ul>
<p>For the purposes of such evaluation, we will NOT collect any personal details which may identify you.</p>
<p><strong>2. Information is collected when you voluntarily provide it.</strong></p>
<p>PFD collects personal information to enable users to access certain sections of the site or participate in promotional offers and other marketing activity. Use and disclosure of personal information in such circumstances will be governed by the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) (as amended) and subject to any terms and conditions or provisions specific to these offers.</p>
<p><strong>3. Use of cookies on this website</strong></p>
<p>This site uses cookies. (A cookie is a small data file that certain web sites write to your computer's hard drive when you visit them.) when a user requests the website to remember password details. Cookies are used only for the purposes of remembering a user’s password and is a voluntary option.</p>
<h2>Returned Merchandise and Refund Policy</h2>
<p>We hope you enjoy our products us much as we do. However, it is important to read our returns and exchanges policy before making any purchases.</p>
<p>If you need to refund or exchange an item, please call  your branch  at the earliest convenience prior to returning the product to us.</p>
<p><strong>Claims</strong></p>
<p>All credit claims must be raised within 48 hours of delivery, including pricing claims.</p>
<p>Drivers are only permitted to collect goods for credit from previous deliveries if advised by PFD in writing.</p>
<p>Memo items (special request off range items) may not be returned for credit.</p>
<p><strong>The return of frozen goods is conditional on the following,</strong></p>
<p>Frozen goods will only be accepted for credit if,</p>
<ul>
<li>Returned on the same day as delivery, or</li>
<li>They are faulty, or</li>
<li>Evidence of cold chain integrity can be provided.</li>
</ul>
<p>All pricing is in Australian Dollars Only (AUD) only</p>
<p><strong>Policy for the non-collection of credit card details</strong></p>
<p>If you pay online using a credit card, the card details are not viewed by us or any person except you during the transaction. The details are encrypted and passed directly to the bank. To find out more information about this site's security information, click here.</p>
<p>We do not retain your credit card details.</p>
<p>We collect site traffic information so we can continually improve site content and design. This does not provide information relating to individual users and only provide generalised information relating to pages viewed by customers.</p>
